WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.000
[Unknown]: I.V.M.

00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:33.000
[Amit Varma]: The driving theme of my life is procrastination.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:34.000
[Amit Varma]: In fact, my epitaph could be,

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:36.000
[Amit Varma]: Here lies a man who waited and waited,

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:38.000
[Amit Varma]: and now the wait is over.

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:40.000
[Amit Varma]: I find it hard to get things started,

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:43.000
[Amit Varma]: or to keep them going once I do get them started.

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:45.000
[Amit Varma]: It was different with the seen and the unseen.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:47.000
[Amit Varma]: When Amit Doshi, who runs I.V.M. podcast,

00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:50.000
[Amit Varma]: came to me and asked if I wanted to do a podcast with him,

00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:51.000
[Amit Varma]: I said no.

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:52.000
[Amit Varma]: I didn't listen to podcasts,

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:54.000
[Amit Varma]: I didn't understand why other people listen to podcasts,

00:00:54.000 --> 00:00:56.000
[Amit Varma]: I wasn't interested.

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:57.000
[Amit Varma]: But he persisted,

00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:00.000
[Amit Varma]: and I mentioned an idea I had for a TV interview show

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:01.000
[Amit Varma]: I wanted to do one day,

00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:03.000
[Amit Varma]: called the seen and the unseen.

00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:05.000
[Amit Varma]: He said, hey, let's do a podcast instead.

00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:06.000
[Amit Varma]: And I figured, yeah,

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:07.000
[Amit Varma]: television wasn't happening anytime soon,

00:01:07.000 --> 00:01:09.000
[Amit Varma]: so why not, let's jump into this.

00:01:09.000 --> 00:01:10.000
[Amit Varma]: We did one episode,

00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:11.000
[Amit Varma]: then another,

00:01:11.000 --> 00:01:12.000
[Amit Varma]: and another.

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:13.000
[Amit Varma]: And here we are now,

00:01:13.000 --> 00:01:15.000
[Amit Varma]: 100 episodes.

00:01:15.000 --> 00:01:17.000
[Amit Varma]: The basic principle that got me here,

00:01:17.000 --> 00:01:19.000
[Amit Varma]: take one step,

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:22.000
[Amit Varma]: and then just keep putting one foot in front of the other.

00:01:22.000 --> 00:01:28.000
[Amit Varma]: There's a life lesson in there that I need to learn from.

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:30.000
[Unknown]: Welcome to the seen and the unseen,

00:01:30.000 --> 00:01:34.000
[Unknown]: our weekly podcast on economics, politics, and behavioral science.

00:01:34.000 --> 00:01:38.000
[Amit Varma]: Please welcome your host, Amit Badma.

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:40.000
[Amit Varma]: Welcome to the seen and the unseen.

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:42.000
[Amit Varma]: How does one celebrate a 100th episode?

00:01:42.000 --> 00:01:44.000
[Amit Varma]: I like to keep celebrations low-key.

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:46.000
[Amit Varma]: I don't like to celebrate my birthday and so on.

00:01:46.000 --> 00:01:49.000
[Amit Varma]: But I thought the least I can do for my 100th episode

00:01:49.000 --> 00:01:51.000
[Amit Varma]: is get a special guest on the show.

00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:54.000
[Amit Varma]: Not some celebrity superstar or a big public intellectual,

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:58.000
[Amit Varma]: but someone with whom I can always reliably have conversations that are special,

00:01:58.000 --> 00:01:59.000
[Amit Varma]: at least for me.

00:01:59.000 --> 00:02:03.000
[Amit Varma]: My guest today is my good friend, Shruti Rajgopalan,

00:02:03.000 --> 00:02:05.000
[Amit Varma]: who teaches economics at Purchase College in New York,

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:07.000
[Amit Varma]: but happens to be here in Mumbai now.

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:10.000
[Amit Varma]: So this is actually going to be a face-to-face conversation,

00:02:10.000 --> 00:02:12.000
[Amit Varma]: unlike the Skype conversations we usually have.

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:15.000
[Amit Varma]: I think this is her 8th appearance on the show,

00:02:15.000 --> 00:02:18.000
[Amit Varma]: and quite apart from the fact that she is so brilliant and insightful.

00:02:18.000 --> 00:02:21.000
[Amit Varma]: I think it might be because she is the one person I know

00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:23.000
[Amit Varma]: whose views are closest to mine.

00:02:23.000 --> 00:02:25.000
[Amit Varma]: We agree with each other on most things,

00:02:25.000 --> 00:02:29.000
[Amit Varma]: which leads to two possible reasons for why I like having her on the show.

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:32.000
[Amit Varma]: One, she validates my sparkling insights.

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:35.000
[Amit Varma]: Two, she confirms my biases.

00:02:35.000 --> 00:02:39.000
[Amit Varma]: I'm inclined to think it's a former, but that could just be my bias.

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:42.000
[Amit Varma]: Before we start shooting the breeze though, a quick commercial break.

